/ File 'SIT-coefficients.dta'.
/
/ Specific Ion interaction model for activity coefficients (the "SIT" model).
/ This file contains parameters (epsilon) to calculate specific ion
/ interactions according to the SIT.  The file contains epsilon values
/ between two species, that is, between cation-anion (or anion-cation),
/ as well as between neutral-cation, neutral-anion and neutral-neutral
/ species.
/
/ In the SIT, for two ions 'i' and 'j', with electric charges Zi and Zj,
/ eps(i,j) = eps(j,i), and eps(i,j) = 0 if (Zi x Zj) > 0.
/
/ The file format is:
/    'first' species name, 'second' species name, epsilon value,
/ where both the first and second species can be either a cation,
/ an anion or a neutral species.
/
/ Last line: must be "end" (witout quotes).
/
/ First non-commented line: if it is "nodefaults" (witout
/ quotes, case-insensitive) then default epsilon values will
/ NOT be gived to ion-interactions where no data has been
/ assigned in this file. The default is to assign default values.
/

nodefaults

/ Note: because of "nodefaults"
/ any eps-values that are not given here will be zero.

/ These are the eps-values that are needed in this case;
/ all values are from the file "sit.dat" distributed with
/ PhreeqC version 3. https://www.usgs.gov/software/phreeqc-version-3
Ca+2, Cl-, 0.14
Cl-, Na+, 0.03
HSO4-, Na+, -0.01
H+, Cl-, 0.12
Na+, OH-, 0.04
SO4-2, Na+, -0.12

/ these values are not given in the Phreeqc database,
/ so we set them to zero:
H+,     SO4-2,  0.
H+,     HSO4-,  0.
Ca+2,    SO4-2, 0.
Ca+2,    HSO4-, 0.
Ca+2,    OH-,   0.
CaOH+,   SO4-2, 0.
CaOH+,   HSO4-, 0.
CaOH+,   Cl-,   0.
CaOH+,   OH-,   0.
OH-,     H+,    0.
CaSO4, Na+,    0.
CaSO4, Cl-,    0.
CaSO4, H+,     0.
CaSO4, SO4-2,  0.
CaSO4, HSO4-,  0.
CaSO4, Ca+2,   0.
CaSO4, CaOH+,  0.
CaSO4, CaSO4,  0.
CaSO4, OH-,    0.

end

